      "text": "228-190: House passed legislation to make foreign nationals inadmissible and noncitizens in the U.S. deportable if they are convicted of, or admit to, harming police animals including dogs and horses. 15 Democrats voted Yes with all Republicans and Rep. Kiley (I-CA), who was recorded as an Independent in the House for the first time since leaving the Republican Party March 9. The BOWOW Act now heads to the Senate.",
